# Replastix Innovations Salesforce Project

## Project Title
RePlastix Innovations: Transforming Plastic Waste into Sustainable Solutions

## Project Overview
Replastix Innovations is a Salesforce-based capstone project developed to automate and streamline the plastic waste recycling business process. The system focuses on inventory management, order processing, stock tracking, replenishment automation, and reporting.

## Business Objective
The goal of this project is to improve operational efficiency by automating key business activities such as:
- Plastic waste recycling management
- Order management
- Inventory monitoring
- Restock request automation
- Approval workflows
- Email notifications
- Reporting and analytics

## Features Implemented

### 1. Data Security
- Created Roles for different users
- Created Profiles for secure access
- Controlled data visibility based on user responsibilities

### 2. Inventory Management
- Tracks product stock levels
- Checks stock threshold automatically
- Creates restock requests when stock is insufficient

### 3. Order Management
- Automatically reduces stock after order creation
- Updates stock records based on order quantity

### 4. Restock Management
- Generates replenishment requests for low stock items
- Approves restock requests
- Updates stock automatically after approval

### 5. Email Notification
- Sends email notification to warehouse manager when restock request is approved

### 6. Reporting
- Supports report and dashboard creation for business analysis

## Salesforce Components Used
- Custom Objects
- Custom Fields
- Roles and Profiles
- Apex Classes
- Apex Triggers
- Validation and Automation
- Reports and Dashboards

## Custom Objects Used
- Re_Plastic_Innovations_Recycled_Product__c
- Re_Plastic_Innovations_Order__c
- Re_Plastic_Innovations_Restock_Request__c

## Apex Components

### Apex Classes
- InventoryManager.cls
- InventoryManagerTest.cls
- EmailNotificationHelper.cls

### Triggers
- UpdateStockAfterOrder.trigger
- UpdateStockAfterRestockApproval.trigger

## Automation Logic
1. When a new order is created:
   - Stock is reduced automatically
   - If stock is insufficient, a restock request is created

2. When a restock request is approved:
   - Product stock is increased automatically
   - Email notification is sent to warehouse manager

